article.headline: George Mason 77, James Madison 58
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Lamar Butler scored 22 points and Tony Skinn added 19 to lead George Mason to a 77-58 win over James Madison on Saturday night. The Patriots (8-8, 3-4 Colonial Athletic Association) led 31-20 at halftime. Their lead was cut to seven twice early in the second half, but they put the game away for good with a 15-3 run that restored their lead to 52-33 with 10:47 remaining. The Dukes (3-12, 1-6) never got closer than 15 again. Jomo Belfor scored 20 points to lead James Madison and Gabriel Chami and Cavell Johnson each added 12. The Dukes shot just 37 percent overall to the Patriots' 50 percent, were outrebounded 39-28 and had just four assists on their 17 baskets. Will Thomas added 12 points and 11 rebounds for George Mason.
